===Etymology 2===
{{IPAchar|/kokono/}} → {{IPAchar|/kono/}}

Abbreviation of {{etyl|ojp|ja}} ''kokono'' (“nine”).

====Pronunciation====
{{ja-pron|acc=1|acc_ref=DJR}}

====Alternative forms====
* {{l|ja|九}}

====Number====
{{ja-pos|numeral symbol}}

# {{lb|ja|dated}} [[nine]]
#: {{ja-usex|ひい、ふう、みい、よう、いつ、むう、なな、やあ、'''この'''、とお。|One, two, three, four, five, six, seven, eight, '''nine''', ten.}}

=====Usage notes=====
Generally only used when counting out loud, as in the example above. In writing, usually found spelled out in hiragana as {{lang|ja|この}} to make the reading unambiguous.

